Package evs.gui.windows

Windows in the GUI.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
GUICommunicator Allows any window to access another window and its associated methods.
GUIInterface A root interface containing methods for saving data permanently to an analysis unit and for storing and displaying temporary data that has not yet been saved.
 

Class Summary
AboutBox Shows the current version, copyright and authorship of EVS.
AggregationA The first aggregation window where the user manages spatial aggregation units and their associated attributes.
ChartDialog Constructs a dialog for displaying an org.jfree.chart.JFreeChart.
Console Constructs a console for showing details of exceptions thrown.
DateSelector Constructs a dialog for date selection.
EVSMainWindow The main window frame for the Ensemble Verification System.
ExceptionHandler Class for informing users about run-time exceptions.
MoreAggParOptionsDialog Constructs a dialog of parameter options for an Aggregation Unit.
MoreInputDialog Dialog for associating scale information with the forecasts and observations.
MoreOutputOptions Constructs a dialog of output options.
MoreParOptionsDialog Constructs a dialog of parameter options
MoreVerificationWindowDialog Dialog for refining the verification window based on date and variable value.
OutputA Window to plot the verification statistics associated with a verification unit or an aggregation unit.
ProductGeneratorDialog Dialog for generating products from metric results.
ProgressMonitor Processing dialog which returns a boolean false on close.
SimpleDialog Constructs a simple dialog with an OK button and a cancel button.
VerificationA First window where Verification Unit's (VUs) are defined and managed.
VerificationB Allows a user to select verification statistics and their associated parameters for a Verification Unit selected in the VerificationA window.
